        <abstract>
            <p>Doubts that glands of calyx of cleistogamic Malpighiaceae serve as protection.</p> 
<p>Some species of <hi rend="italic">Solanum</hi> bear long- and short-styled flowers on same plant.</p> 
            <p>Changing colours of some flowers may show insects the proper moment for fertilisation.</p> 
<p>Doubts that the style of <hi rend="italic">Pontederia cordata</hi> changes length.</p> 
            <p>Sexual difference in wings of some butterflies due to development in male of scales that emit odours to excite female.</p>
        </abstract>
